<seg id=1> Nearly 100 Foreign Capital Enterprises in Tianjin Development Zone Become Customs Bonded Factories </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Tianjin, December 27, Telegram.  This reporter has learned from Tianjin Customs that 20 foreign investment enterprises, including Tongyong Semiconductor (China) Co., Ltd., recently received approval from Tianjin Customs and became bonded factories under a preferential tax policy. </seg>
<seg id=3> As of now, the Tianjin Economic Technology Development Zone has 99 foreign capital enterprises that have become bonded factories. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> According to information provided, Tianjin Customs have been actively connecting up with customary international practice in recent years, strengthening macroscopic business management, optimizing the customs environment, prompting businesses to more efficiently engage in trade, and forcefully promoting the bonded project system. </seg>
<seg id=5> The Economic Technology Development Zone serves as a growing point for the local economy, and the processing trade is developing rapidly.  Currently, there are already 22 foreign capital enterprises engaging in the processing trade.  Bonded factories already account for 41 percent of the total number of enterprises, and have gradually formed a bonded factory system involving industries such as electronics, chemical engineering, textiles, communications, and automobiles.  Motorola, Samsung Electronics, Yamaha, and others are all members. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Based on information from a Tianjin Development Zone customs official, bonded factories reduce trade costs and increase trade benefits. </seg>
<seg id=7> Since becoming a bonded factory, Tongyong Semiconductor (China) Co., Ltd. has reduced the amount of circulating capital it uses by US$500,000 a day. </seg>
<seg id=8> The company stated that in the next five years it will invest an additional US$90 million, and estimated that the value of annual production when that has been completed could reach US$300 million. </seg>
</p>
